# Copy to .env and adjust. See docs/platforms.md for YouTube upload OAuth.

# FFmpeg: optional explicit paths. If unset, the backend uses PATH, then (macOS) /opt/homebrew/bin and
# /usr/local/bin, then (Windows) registry Path + common install dirs (WinGet, Scoop, Chocolatey).
# Verify discovery: GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/health -> ffmpeg_ok and resolved paths (see README Prerequisites).
# This file is always loaded from backend/.env (not the current working directory).
# Use the same folder for both (typical winget: ...\ffmpeg-8.1-full_build\bin\ffmpeg.exe).
# Helper: powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\print-ffmpeg-paths.ps1
# FFMPEG_PATH=C:\Users\YOU\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WinGet\Packages\Gyan.FFmpeg_*\ffmpeg-*\bin\ffmpeg.exe
# FFPROBE_PATH=C:\Users\YOU\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WinGet\Packages\Gyan.FFmpeg_*\ffmpeg-*\bin\ffprobe.exe

# Clip suggestion: heuristic (default) or embeddings (pip install -r requirements-ml.txt).
# SUGGEST_ENGINE=embeddings
# SENTENCE_TRANSFORMER_MODEL=all-MiniLM-L6-v2

# CORS (comma-separated origins)
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173

# YouTube ingest: if downloads return 403 or SABR issues, use cookies while logged in.
# On Windows, Chrome/Edge often fail with DPAPI; prefer a Netscape cookies.txt file:
# YTDLP_COOKIES_FILE=C:\path\to\youtube_cookies.txt
# Or try Firefox's cookie store:
# YTDLP_COOKIES_FROM_BROWSER=firefox

# YouTube Shorts direct upload (optional)
# YOUTUBE_CLIENT_SECRETS_PATH=C:\path\to\client_secret.json
# YOUTUBE_TOKEN_PATH=C:\path\to\youtube_token.json
